Stena, KKR Interested to Buy Istanbul Ferry Company, Dunya Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-02-11T06:52:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/stena-kkr-interested-to-buy-istanbul-ferry-company-dunya-says.html
Stena AB, a Swedish shipping
company, and U.S. private equity firm  KKR & Co LP  and are among
those interested to acquire Istanbul’s ferry operator,  Dunya 
said, without saying where it got the information.    TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS , Turkey’s biggest airport
operator, Istanbul-based Fiba Holding AS,  Koc Holding AS , Boydak
Group, Zorlu Group are also interested in buying Istanbul Deniz
Otobusleri Sanayi & Ticaret AS, known as IDO, it said.  Istanbul’s municipality said on Jan.4 it expects to get
bids to sell its 100 percent stake in IDO by March 31.  Greece’s Maritime Company of Lesvos and its Turkish private
equity firm Rhea Girisim Sermayesi Yatirim Ortakligi AS will put
a joint bid in the auction, Rhea said on Feb 9.  Interested companies must have at least $200 million of
sales in 2010 and private equity firms must manage at least $200
million of assets to be able to bid in the auction, Dunya said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 